# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Lead Scraping Tool — Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your real API keys.
# Never commit the actual .env file to version control.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── REQUIRED ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Google Places API key
# How to get it:
#   1. Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/
#   2. Create a project (or select an existing one).
#   3. Enable "Places API" (legacy) under "APIs & Services > Library".
#   4. Create credentials → API Key.
#   5. (Recommended) Restrict the key to the Places API only.
#
# Free tier: Google provides $200 USD/month of free credit, which covers
# roughly 11 000 Place Details calls or 6 000 Text Search calls per month.
GOOGLE_API_KEY=your_google_places_api_key_here

# ── OPTIONAL — only required when using --use-ai ──────────────────────────────
# OpenAI API key (gpt-3.5-turbo is used to keep costs minimal)
# How to get it:
#   1. Sign up at https://platform.openai.com/
#   2. Go to API Keys and create a new key.
#   3. Paste it below.
#
# If this key is absent or the API call fails, the tool automatically falls
# back to standard mode — no manual intervention needed.
OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key_here
